{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QNATkPccH5iezQo1f5mfXB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to compile the compliance audit findings. Let me analyze what I've found:\n\n**RBAC:**\n- ServiceAccount `spark-pi` exists (custom, non-default)\n- Role `spark-pi-role` with limited verbs (create, get, list, watch, delete, update, patch) on services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims\n- RoleBinding `spark-pi-role-binding` binds the role to the `spark-pi` ServiceAccount\n- Default ServiceAccount also exists but is not used by workloads\n\n**What is correctly configured:**\nAll workloads use the custom `spark-pi` ServiceAccount instead of the default, the Role is namespace-scoped rather than cluster-wide, resource limits and requests are defined across all containers, the Spark image version is pinned to 3.5.3 instead of using latest, and the job is configured with no automatic retries and a Never restart policy.\n\n**Gaps/Findings:**\nI'm now identifying the security gaps, starting with Pod Security Context — none of the three workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi job) appear to have security contexts defined. The RBAC role grants overly permissive write access including destructive operations like deleting PVCs and modifying configmaps. There's no NetworkPolicy restricting pod-to-pod communication or access to the Spark master's web UI and protocol ports. The deployment uses tag-based image references without digest pinning, and pulls from public registries without authentication, both of which could allow image tampering. The Spark web UI on port 8080 is exposed without TLS or authentication controls, and the spark-pi job pod also lacks proper security context configuration.\n\nNow I'm identifying what's actually configured correctly versus the gaps that need addressing.\n\nThe Role is appropriately restrictive, limiting access to only services, configmaps, and PVCs without granting dangerous permissions like pod exec or secret access. But there are several security gaps: all the pods are missing security contexts entirely—no non-root user enforcement, no read-only filesystems, no capability dropping, or seccomp profiles. There's also no NetworkPolicy to restrict traffic between the Spark components, leaving the master's web UI and protocol ports open within the cluster. And the RBAC grants some overly permissive write verbs, like delete on PVCs, which could be destructive.\n\nOn the image side, the manifests use specific tags but not digest pinning, so tag mutation attacks are possible. The imagePullPolicy is set to IfNotPresent, which means a compromised local cache won't be refreshed. Plus there's no imagePullSecrets configured, so images are pulled anonymously from Docker Hub with no authentication. Finally, the Spark Master's web UI on port 8080 is exposed without any TLS or authentication layer enforced at the network level.\n\nNow I'm documenting these findings and setting up the ConfigMap.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1544,"cache_read_input_tokens":31950,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1544},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"502f4f6c-0c46-4732-b960-fa8bffe19ad6","uuid":"bfd1879d-cda0-443a-aafe-8c28eb9ebda3","request_id":"req_011CcLBVM1Fd7VnXkCtAxr7h"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QNATkPccH5iezQo1f5mfXB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the data needed. Let me compile and save the findings."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1544,"cache_read_input_tokens":31950,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1544},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"502f4f6c-0c46-4732-b960-fa8bffe19ad6","uuid":"cfc5bf45-c07e-444c-b8c0-91fdccfc5934","request_id":"req_011CcLBVM1Fd7VnXkCtAxr7h"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QNATkPccH5iezQo1f5mfXB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01F3oCMvMLRZYbqQRsFwHhj5","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"SPARK-PI NAMESPACE COMPLIANCE AUDIT\nDate: 2026-06-23\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection\nScope: RBAC, resource limits, image provenance, job security context, network policies\n\n=== CORRECTLY CONFIGURED ===\n\n[PASS] Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  A non-default ServiceAccount 'spark-pi' is created and used by all three\n  workloads (spark-master deployment, spark-worker deployment, spark-pi job).\n  The 'default' SA is not bound to any role and is not used.\n\n[PASS] Namespace-scoped RBAC Role (no ClusterRole)\n  Role 'spark-pi-role' is namespace-scoped (kind: Role, not ClusterRole).\n  Blast radius is confined to the spark-pi namespace.\n\n[PASS] RoleBinding correctly scoped\n  RoleBinding 'spark-pi-role-binding' binds 'spark-pi-role' only to the\n  'spark-pi' ServiceAccount in the 'spark-pi' namespace. No wildcard subjects.\n\n[PASS] RBAC resource scope limited\n  The role grants access only to services, configmaps, and\n  persistentvolumeclaims. No access to pods, secrets, nodes, or cluster-level\n  resources. No 'exec' or 'portforward' verbs.\n\n[PASS] CPU and memory requests/limits set on all containers\n  spark-master:  requests cpu=200m, memory=512Mi  |  limits cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\n  spark-worker:  requests cpu=200m, memory=512Mi  |  limits cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\n  spark-pi job:  requests cpu=200m, memory=512Mi  |  limits cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\n  All containers have both requests and limits defined; no unbounded resource usage.\n\n[PASS] Specific image tag pinned (no 'latest')\n  All three workloads use 'apache/spark:3.5.3'. The 'latest' tag is not used.\n\n[PASS] Job backoff and restart policy hardened\n  spark-pi Job has backoffLimit=0 and restartPolicy=Never, preventing\n  uncontrolled retry loops on failure.\n\n=== GAPS / FINDINGS ===\n\n[FAIL] No pod-level or container-level securityContext on any workload\n  All three workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi job) have an\n  empty pod securityContext ({}) and no container-level securityContext at all.\n  Missing controls:\n    - runAsNonRoot: true  (containers may run as root/UID 0)\n    - runAsUser / runAsGroup  (no explicit UID/GID enforced)\n    - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false  (privilege escalation not blocked)\n    - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true  (writable root FS on all containers)\n    - capabilities.drop: [ALL]  (Linux capabilities not dropped)\n    - seccompProfile  (no seccomp profile applied)\n  Affected: spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, spark-pi Job.\n\n[FAIL] No NetworkPolicy in the namespace\n  No NetworkPolicy objects exist in spark-pi. All pods can freely communicate\n  with any pod in any namespace, and can receive connections from anywhere in\n  the cluster. Specifically:\n    - Spark master Web UI (port 8080) is reachable cluster-wide.\n    - Spark protocol port (7077) is reachable cluster-wide.\n    - No egress restrictions on any pod.\n\n[FAIL] RBAC write verbs are broader than necessary\n  'spark-pi-role' grants create, update, patch, and delete on configmaps,\n  services, and persistentvolumeclaims. The 'delete' verb on PVCs is\n  destructive and irreversible. If the Spark job only needs to read existing\n  resources, the verbs should be trimmed to get/list/watch only for each\n  resource type actually required at runtime.\n\n[FAIL] No image digest pinning\n  Images are referenced by mutable tag ('apache/spark:3.5.3') rather than by\n  immutable SHA-256 digest (e.g., apache/spark@sha256:<hash>). A mutable tag\n  can be overwritten in the registry, allowing a supply-chain attack to replace\n  the image without changing the manifest.\n\n[FAIL] imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent combined with tag-only reference\n  With IfNotPresent, Kubernetes will not re-pull the image if any layer is\n  already cached locally. This means a tampered or stale cached image will be\n  used silently. Using 'Always' together with digest pinning would ensure the\n  correct image is used on every pod start.\n\n[FAIL] No imagePullSecrets configured\n  All images are pulled anonymously from Docker Hub. Anonymous pulls are\n  subject to rate limiting and provide no cryptographic proof of registry\n  identity. A private registry with authenticated pulls would improve both\n  availability and provenance assurance.\n\n=== SUMMARY ===\n\nCorrectly configured: 7 controls (dedicated SA, namespace-scoped RBAC,\n  binding scope, resource limits on all containers, specific image tag,\n  job backoff/restart policy, no cluster-level role).\n\nGaps requiring remediation: 6 findings (missing securityContext on all\n  workloads, no NetworkPolicy, overly broad RBAC write verbs, no digest\n  pinning, IfNotPresent pull policy risk, no imagePullSecrets).\n\nHighest severity: missing securityContext (containers may run as root with\n  full Linux capabilities and writable filesystems) and missing NetworkPolicy\n  (unrestricted lateral movement within cluster).\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with compliance findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1544,"cache_read_input_tokens":31950,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1544},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"502f4f6c-0c46-4732-b960-fa8bffe19ad6","uuid":"d4558e6c-68d1-422c-847e-070c6a2db43d","request_id":"req_011CcLBVM1Fd7VnXkCtAxr7h"}
